# Declarative Pipeline ğŸ“

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm ci'
                sh 'npm run build'
            }
        }

        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm test'
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy') {
            steps {
                sh './deploy.sh'
            }
        }
    }

    post {
        success {
            echo 'Pipeline succeeded!'
        }
    }
}
```

# Pipeline Syntax ğŸ“

## Stages & Steps

```groovy
stages {
    stage('Build') {
        steps {
            sh 'echo Hello'
            echo 'Building...'
        }
    }
}
```

## Common Steps

| Step | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `sh` | Run shell command |
| `bat` | Run Windows batch |
| `echo` | Print message |
| `dir` | Change directory |
| `checkout` | Clone repository |

# Jenkins Agents ğŸ¤–

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    // Or specific label
    agent { label 'linux' }

    // Or Docker
    agent {
        docker {
            image 'node:20-alpine'
        }
    }
}
```

## Agent Types

| Setting | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `any` | Any available |
| `none` | No global agent |
| `label` | Specific label |
| `docker` | Container |

# Parallel Builds âš¡

```groovy
stage('Test') {
    parallel {
        stage('Unit') {
            steps { sh 'npm test:unit' }
        }
        stage('E2E') {
            steps { sh 'npm test:e2e' }
        }
    }
}
```

